<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<div class="nbs-page-header" id="n40144"> <h4 class="sheetno">Page: <a name="n40" href="../../ff/fdra/fnbdetails.htm#n40">N40 (VI.B.28B)  144</a></h4> <mm class="note">Note: The &ldquo;tragic carpet&rdquo; was the green baize stage cloth or carpet used in English theatre (17th-19th centuries) to protect the costumes of dying characters in tragedy. It was carried onstage, when required, by two persons unassociated with the play. </mm> </div>
